IGL_Renderable
public class BezierCurve
extends Shape

This class draws a Bezier curve using the specified control points. The shape of the Bezier curve is determined by forming weighted averages of the points in the array of control points. By default, the curve will be evaluated using 10 intermediate points. The number of points to use to evaluate the curve can be set by calling the setNum_steps() method. NOTE: The number of control points must not exceed the value specified by the OpenGL constant GL_MAX_EVAL_ORDER. The maximum number points allowed depends on the OpenGL implementation, but must be at least 8. This is checked when the is rendered, and a warning message will be printed if the maximum is exceeded.
